entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
[virtual-signal=signal-P] = Base Priority
[virtual-signal=signal-L] = Trainloads Missing
Calculates Priority as [virtual-signal=signal-P] + [virtual-signal=signal-L]

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
[item=parameter-1] = How many more [item=parameter-1] can fit in the buffer
[virtual-signal=signal-C] = Total Train Capacity
Calculates [virtual-signal=signal-L] as total missing trainloads

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
[virtual-signal=signal-T] = Total Buffer Capacity
[item=parameter-1] = Requested Item
Calculates how many more [item=parameter-1] can fit in the buffer

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description:
[item=parameter-3] = Requested item
[virtual-signal=signal-P] = base priority
[virtual-signal=signal-W] = cargo wagons
[virtual-signal=signal-S] = cargo wagon slots
W*S*[item=parameter-3]=[virtual-signal=signal-C] = total train cargo capacity
[virtual-signal=signal-B] = buffer chests per wagon
[virtual-signal=signal-H] = chest slots
B*H*[item=parameter-3]=[virtual-signal=signal-T] = total buffer capacity

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
[virtual-signal=signal-L] = Missing Trainloads
Sets Train Limit to 1 if at least 1 trainload can fit
(there's no stacker so train limit max = 1)
